It must be observed, that in Twysden's edition of Knygffion, as likewise in the printed text of the Rolls of Parliament, the term has been given as Lussheburne, apparently in consequence of its origin having been forgotten; it seems, however, evident that the true reading should be Lussheburue, which is merely a variation from Lussheburwe, or Lucyn- burgh.
